# QA & testing

## Test pyramid

1. **Unit** (`composeApp/src/commonTest`) — fast, deterministic; fake repositories/services.
2. **Instrumented** (`androidApp/src/androidInstrumentedTest`) — Compose UI smoke on critical paths.
3. **Manual** (`firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml`) — Firebase App Distribution testers (currently **v76**).

## Test coverage mandate (non-negotiable)

Every code change — bug fix, feature, or refactor — **must** satisfy all applicable rules below before the task is considered done. This is a merge blocker equivalent to i18n parity.

### Adding new code

| What you add | Required test |
|---|---|
| New domain model method / pure function | Unit test covering happy path + at least one edge/error case |
| New repository method | Unit test via `Fake*` repository; assert state emitted by `Flow` or return value |
| New screen model method / state transition | `runTest` + `TestDispatcher`; call the method, `advanceUntilIdle()`, assert `StateFlow` value |
| New codec / mapper | Unit test round-tripping domain ↔ DTO |
| New composable screen | Add `*TestTags` constants; add instrumented smoke test for the primary tap path |
| New `LazyColumn` / `LazyRow` `items()` block | Key must be a stable unique identifier; use type-prefix (`"invite-"`, `"member-"`, `"done-"`) when multiple `items()` blocks share the same column |
| New i18n string key | Covered by `*LocaleStringsTest` automatically once added to all 8 locale files |

### Modifying existing code

| What you change | Required test update |
|---|---|
| Change a domain/screen model method signature or behavior | Update every unit test that calls it; add a new case if the change introduces a new code path |
| Change a repository or service interface | Update **all** `Fake*` implementations (`FakeAuthRepository`, `FakeNutritionRepository`, instrumented fakes, etc.) to match the new API, then verify tests still compile and pass |
| Change a composable's visible output / UX state | Update or add the matching instrumented or unit assertion |
| Change navigation routes or `AppNavigator` API | Update `AppNavigatorTest`, `AppNavigationTest`, and any contract tests |
| Change a codec / DTO shape | Update the round-trip unit test to cover the new shape |
| Remove a feature or screen | Delete its test file; remove orphan `testTag` references and Firebase YAML entries |

### Keeping fakes in sync

- Fakes must implement the **full** interface — never leave unimplemented stubs (`TODO()`) in shipped fake code.
- When a method is added to a domain interface, update every fake in `commonTest/…/presentation/di/` and `androidInstrumentedTest/…/` immediately in the same commit as the interface change.
- CI will fail to compile if a fake is incomplete; treat that as P0.

## Unit tests

- Pure domain: no mocks (`NutritionAiPlanner`, `WeekCalendar`, `GroceryListPresentation`, codecs).
- Screen models: `runTest` + `TestDispatcher`; `advanceUntilIdle()` after `scope.launch` updates.
- Fakes must implement **full** interfaces — update when APIs grow (`FakeAuthRepository`, instrumented fakes).
- **i18n parity:** `*LocaleStringsTest` (Auth, Home, Nutrition, Household, Sharing) — every key in all 8 locales.
- **Navigation:** `AppNavigatorTest`, `AppNavigationTest`, `HouseholdNavigationContractTest`.
- **Theme:** `AppIconsTest` — no broken semantic aliases.
- **Invite/collab:** parsers, OTP, preview RPC; Deno tests for edge pure helpers.

```bash
./gradlew :composeApp:testDebugUnitTest
```

## Instrumented tests

- `createAndroidComposeRule` + `AppTheme` + `InstrumentedKoinHost` / `InstrumentedNutritionFakes`.
- `onNodeWithTag` over text; `performScrollTo` before off-screen nodes.
- `InstrumentedComposeTest.waitFor` / `waitUntil` — no `Thread.sleep`.
- Scope: integration smoke (navigation, grocery add, meal-plan AI button, hub cards, touch targets).
- Deep CRUD rules belong in `NutritionScreenModelTest` / domain unit tests.

```bash
./gradlew :androidApp:assembleDebugAndroidTest
```

CI runs instrumented on PR and `main` push; local optional via emulator.

## Manual QA (Firebase)

Update `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` when user-visible flows change:

- Bump top-level `version` and `updated` date.
- Add `id`, `title`, `steps`, `expected` per scenario.
- Distinguish editable grocery vs AI read-only (terracotta) suggestions.
- Wave C cases: `wavec-dark-theme-napolitan`, `wavec-wide-grocery-side-panel`, `wavec-wide-meal-plan-columns`, `wavec-ai-grocery-terracotta-accent`.
- Hub: grocery + meal plan entry; back returns to hub.
- Crashlytics: `crashlytics-smoke` on builds with `google-services.json`.
- Household: `household-member-avatar` — member row photos, self + dependant upload (requires `member-avatars` bucket + migration `20250703000000`).

Release workflow embeds checklist excerpt in Firebase release notes.

## Before merge (every PR — mandatory)

Run **both** commands and confirm green before declaring done:

```bash
./gradlew :composeApp:testDebugUnitTest
./gradlew :composeApp:compileDebugAndroidTestKotlinAndroid
```

- **Unit tests must pass** — `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` with zero failures.
- **Instrumented compile must succeed** — catches broken fakes, missing `testTag`s, and API mismatches before CI.
- A PR where either command produces `BUILD FAILED` must not be submitted for review.

When touching invites/migrations:

```bash
./scripts/test-supabase-invite-edge.sh
./scripts/verify-supabase-household.sh   # staging, needs credentials
```

## Test naming

- Unit: `*Test.kt` under mirrored package path.
- Instrumented: `*InstrumentedTest.kt` in `androidInstrumentedTest/.../ui/`.
- Fakes: `Fake*` / `Instrumented*Fakes.kt`.
